Description: Near Bermuda Run / Mile Marker 180 to 180 Heading West. The Contractor for the I-0911A project (I-40 over the Yadkin River at the Davie-Forsyth County Line) will close various ramps at NC801 (Exit 180) near Bermuda Run. On Wednesday Night (7/21) the contractor will close the off-ramp from I-40 Westbound to NC801 South from 10:00PM - 2:00AM and the on-ramp from NC 801 to I-40 Westbound from 2:00AM - 7:00AM.&nbsp; These ramp closures are necessary to safely place asphalt pavement on the ramps. Detours will be utilized for these ramp closure. A link to the detour maps is provided below.&nbsp;This work is part of the&nbsp;continuing construction to&nbsp;replace the I-40 bridges over the Yadkin River and to widen and make improvements along I-40.&nbsp;As always this work is weather dependent and may be subject to change.
